About Us
Our goal is to enable a world in which important data is always protected, available and useful.
Our business may be in the cloud, but we're grounded by the belief that what we do matters. Read on to find out more about Carbonite and the people who help us protect what matters and keep businesses in business.














Over 500 billion files backed up and counting















Fast facts

Founded in 2005 — that makes us a cloud pioneer
Proudly headquartered in Boston, Mass., with offices in Lewiston, Maine; Sunnyvale and San Francisco, Calif.; Salt Lake City, Utah; Oakville, Ontario; Den Bosch, Netherlands; and Munich and Viersen, Germany
More than 800 talented team members protecting our customers' data
Data centers in multiple locations
We've recovered more than 40 billion files since 2005, 9 billion in 2014 alone













Our guiding pillars
Your files are more than computer documents. They are the foundation of your business, wedding photos, first drafts of your novel and so much more. That's why we take backup seriously. Read more about the pillars that guide us every day.
View our guiding pillars








Our solutions are enterprise-grade, but designed to meet the needs of small businesses and individuals.



Our products are easy to use and own so you can spend less time thinking about your backup and more time focused on what matters.



Our products give you everything you need, and nothing you don't — at an affordable and predictable price.



Our proven, innovative technology protects your data and provides peace of mind.













Why couldn't someone offer backup that was simple and affordable? 

That idea became Carbonite.
Read Our Story











