Carbonite (online backup)

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

Carbonite is an online backup service, available to Windows and macOS users, that backs up documents, e-mails, music, photos, and settings.[1] It is named after carbonite, the fictional substance used to freeze Han Solo in Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back.[2] It was the first such service to offer unlimited backup space for a fixed price.[3] Previously, all online backup services were priced by the gigabyte; many other vendors[which?] have since changed to an unlimited model.
Carbonite offers two separate lines of products: Carbonite Home and Home Office for individuals, families, and one- or two-person businesses; and Carbonite Small Business for businesses with three or more computers.[4]
Carbonite was named "Best Windows Backup Tool" by Lifehacker,[5] "Labs Winner" by PC Pro, "Editor's Choice" by NextAdvisor,[6] Hottest Boston Company by Lead411,[7] but received only "two mice" in a MacWorld review putting it second to last.[8]



